# Prisma client Subsciption $fragments for sub types

**Article Title (if relevant)**
[https://www.prisma.io/docs/prisma-client/features/realtime-JAVASCRIPT-rsc8/](url)

**Describe the content issue**
Using prisma client I can't find a way to pass **$fragment** in subscriptions
For example the following subscription 

`prisma.subscribe.post({
     node: {
           createdAt_lte: "DATETIME"
     }
}).node()`

I want to get the mutation type, the posts and the comments for this post

**Describe the solution you'd like to see**
With prisma binding I was able to pass the info or any fragments I need like this

`prisma.subscription.post({
     where {
          node: {
                createdAt_lte: "DATETIME"
          }
     }
}, '{ 
          mutation
           previousValues { id } 
          node { id status comments { id title } }
     }')`

Is there Anyway to do the same with prisma client to get the mutation, and sub fields in the response?

